Organization Name: Las Cumbres Observatory Global Telescope Network
Description: LCOGT is a non-profit, building and operating a network of professional robotic telescopes, deployed worldwide, for science and education.
Full Description: Las Cumbres Observatory Global Telescope Network (LCOGT, Inc.) is a 501(c)(3) non-profit, building and operating a network of professional robotic telescopes, deployed worldwide, for science and education. Their users include professional astronomers, school children and interested members of the public. It is their goal to be a world-class scientific organization, while enabling a new generation of young people to explore the process of science and scientific thinking, through hands-on astronomy.  Their professional users include the members of their Science Collaboration, a set of institutions that has helped us build their network. The LCOGT staff includes astronomers, engineers, and technical, logistical, and administrative personnel.  Their headquarters is in Goleta, California, and they have additional personnel in Liverpool and Cardiff in the United Kingdom, and at Siding Spring Observatory and Haleakala Observatory, in Australia and Hawaii respectively. Their network capabilities emphasize the unique requirements of time-domain astrophysics.  Their instrumentation is designed to allow seamless integration of data from multiple telescopes.  Observations are carried out by fully-robotic, on-site systems that are fed by a single network scheduler.  They support the scheduling of sequences of observations (over all cadences and time periods) as well as rapid-response targets of opportunity.

Description: VitaCig, Inc. – Leveraging Mobile Vaporization for Medical Delivery Applications
Full Description: VitaCig, Inc. an mCig, Inc. (Stock Symbol: MCIG) Company, is a technology company that is harnessing mobile vaporization technology for medical delivery applications. The company  launched its first consumer product: The VitaCig, a $3 nicotine-free device that looks and feels like an electronic cigarette (eCig). Unlike a traditional eCig, the VitaCig delivers a water-vapor of natural flavors, vitamins, and phytonutrients. Initially the VitaCig will be produced in three flavor categories: Relax, Refresh, Energize with plans for additional flavor categories and targeted medical applications in the future.   Thinking Outside The Box The traditional tobacco industry is estimated at nearly $900 Billion a year. Financial analysts from Wells Fargo, Goldman Sachs, and Citigroup predict that by 2022 Electronic Cigarettes will supplant the traditional tobacco industry and eventually grow into a $1 Trillion industry. A Unique Product at the Right Time The VitaCig is the right product unveiled at the right time. Society is well educated as to the negative effects of traditional smoking yet at the same time genuinely confused as to whether electronic cigarettes as currently marketed represent a true improvement in health or are simply gimmicks disguising the delivery of nicotine. By removing nicotine entirely from the equation and delivering vitamins and nutrients instead, VitaCig is well-positioned to gain both the trust and acceptance of consumers around the world. Strategic Investment VitaCig, Inc. is 49% owned by mCig, Inc. (Stock Symbol: MCIG) a technology company that has a history of disrupting the traditional eCig industry by bringing to market the mCig, a $10 loose-leaf eCig. Simultaneously Disrupting Big Tobacco and Big Pharma VitaCig, Inc. is disrupting both the traditional tobacco industry and the growing electronic cigarette industry by appealing to the existing 1.2 Billion adults globally that smoke cigarettes, providing them with a nicotine and tobacco-free alternative that may assist in harm reduction. Moreover, the company is expanding the target market beyond the 1.2 Billion adults by appealing to non-smokers or occasional smokers with a superior method for the consumption of Vitamins, Nutrients, and other compounds with medicinal efficacy.

Full Description: Every company has a story and many of Their customers are curious to know how Apples of Gold came to be a main contender in the online jewelry market. Since shopping with us and getting to know us isn’t quite as simple as wandering into the jewelry shop and chatting over the glass cases, They strive to give that personal, relational feel by telling a little of Their company’s story and background.  Apples of Gold launched its online presence on the premise that traditional jewelers are overpriced. Markups can range anywhere from 100-300%.  Seeing the jewelry prices in high-end retail jewelry stores as exorbitant and plainly unfair, Apples of Gold dared to believe there was a better way. Branching off of a Los Angeles jewelry wholesaler with over 25 years of experience in the jewelry industry, Apples of Gold launched in the year 2000 with the resolute promise of providing the same, high-end jewelry as any successful jewelry retailer, but at a dramatically lower price.
